1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,340
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,340 --> 00:00:02,340
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:03,340
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:06,510
The true culprit behind...

5
00:00:06,510 --> 00:00:08,210
the Temi Bio case
from seven years ago is...

6
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:21,190
(To Yu Na's Mom and to Yu Na)

7
00:00:21,460 --> 00:00:22,460
Park Tae Ho?

8
00:00:23,130 --> 00:00:24,130
The culprit is...

9
00:00:24,830 --> 00:00:26,600
not Chairman Park Tae Ho,
but Choi Sam Sik,

10
00:00:27,170 --> 00:00:28,230
my father.

11
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:32,800
- Choi Sam Sik?
- Hold on.

12
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,910
- What's going on?
- It wasn't Chairman Park?

13
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:36,440
What's the truth?

14
00:00:37,580 --> 00:00:39,240
- That's impossible.
- Are you saying it wasn't him?

15
00:00:39,310 --> 00:00:41,950
- Is what you've just said true?
- Snap out of it, Choi Yu Na.

16
00:00:42,780 --> 00:00:44,220
How could you frame
your own father...

17
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:45,780
as a murderer
instead of Park Tae Ho?

18
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,650
- Please, continue.
- It wasn't Park Tae Ho?

19
00:00:47,850 --> 00:00:50,020
- Is there any truth to this?
- Just tell us the truth.

20
00:00:53,490 --> 00:00:54,630
Tell us who the real culprit is.

21
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,970
You're right, sir.

22
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,540
Whether my father is in prison...

23
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,040
or dead,

24
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:11,310
it's fine as long as it benefits me.

25
00:01:12,180 --> 00:01:15,280
Then announce it to the press.

26
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:16,380
Before I do,

27
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:20,390
we need to be clear about
my compensation first.

28
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:22,920
Come on, as for compensation,

29
00:01:23,290 --> 00:01:25,460
- it'll be as I promised...
- No.

30
00:01:26,790 --> 00:01:29,960
I can't trust a verbal promise.

31
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:33,230
You also promised
to let me marry Min Jun,

32
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,500
but you broke that promise
in the end.

33
00:01:35,930 --> 00:01:36,940
So?

34
00:01:37,470 --> 00:01:39,370
The recorder pen with my confession.

35
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:41,540
Give it to me right now.

36
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:45,940
I also want the money
to settle the seizure,

37
00:01:46,380 --> 00:01:48,380
plus the Adele stock.

38
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:49,880
And lastly,

39
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:54,190
approve my marriage
to Park Hyun Jun.

40
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:56,720
You want stock
and my approval for marriage?

41
00:01:58,020 --> 00:02:00,790
That's a steep price
for Choi Sam Sik's life.

42
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:07,430
It's not the price
of my father's life.

43
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,170
It's the price of saving yours, sir.

44
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,770
My father is taking your place
as a murderer,

45
00:02:14,370 --> 00:02:15,370
so you have to pay up.

46
00:02:32,090 --> 00:02:33,990
Jin Ju, I'm sorry.

47
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,730
Your father...

48
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,630
It was my father, not Chairman Park.

49
00:02:42,730 --> 00:02:44,040
My father killed him.

50
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:46,910
Choi Yu Na.

51
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:51,280
What lies are you telling?

52
00:02:51,710 --> 00:02:52,710
I'm sorry.

53
00:02:53,510 --> 00:02:54,880
On my father's behalf,

54
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:00,180
I ask for your forgiveness.

55
00:03:01,650 --> 00:03:04,360
Ms. Baek,
Choi Yu Na is lying, isn't she?

56
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:06,790
Did the documentary name
the wrong culprit by mistake?

57
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:09,230
Do you still believe
that Chairman Park is the culprit?

58
00:03:09,330 --> 00:03:10,960
Aren't you just using
a past incident...

59
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:12,460
to frame Chairman Park Tae Ho?

60
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:13,500
That's not true.

61
00:03:14,070 --> 00:03:16,200
The person who killed my father
is Park Tae Ho.

62
00:03:16,770 --> 00:03:18,500
Choi Yu Na is lying.

63
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:19,770
Is that true?

64
00:03:20,270 --> 00:03:21,270
Are you sure?

65
00:03:21,570 --> 00:03:24,340
As Chairman Park Tae Ho's son,
I can say with certainty.

66
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:28,310
Everything in the Temi Bio
exposé documentary is true.

67
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,280
Jin Ju.

68
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:34,750
- Is that Choi Yu Na?
- Was the documentary a lie?

69
00:03:36,590 --> 00:03:37,590
Please, tell us.

70
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:40,660
Stop filming. That's enough.
This isn't going to solve anything.

71
00:03:40,730 --> 00:03:42,190
I said that's enough. Stop it.

72
00:03:44,030 --> 00:03:45,200
Please leave.

73
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,970
- Please tell us.
- Tell us the truth.

74
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:51,700
- Is there any credibility to this?
- Just tell us the truth.

75
00:03:51,770 --> 00:03:52,770
What's the truth?

76
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:54,210
Do you still believe
Chairman Park is the culprit?

77
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,440
Tell us the truth!

78
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:58,840
What's your position on this?

79
00:04:01,810 --> 00:04:03,950
Please tell us. Tell us the truth.

80
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:10,190
What did Park Tae Ho
threaten you with?

81
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:14,230
How could you protect Park Tae Ho,
the man who killed your father,

82
00:04:14,390 --> 00:04:17,300
and frame your innocent father
as a murderer?

83
00:04:24,770 --> 00:04:26,100
Watch what you say.

84
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:28,640
The person who killed my dad
wasn't the chairman.

85
00:04:29,810 --> 00:04:31,140
It was you, Baek Jin Ju.

86
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:32,740
What?

87
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:34,910
If my dad had turned himself in
and gone to prison,

88
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:35,980
he wouldn't have died.

89
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:39,150
But you stepped in and pushed him
to betray the chairman.

90
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:41,590
That's why my dad died.

91
00:04:42,190 --> 00:04:45,820
He died
because you pushed him to fight.

92
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:48,390
That's ridiculous.

93
00:04:48,990 --> 00:04:51,860
Park Tae Ho killed your dad,
so why are you blaming someone else?

94
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:54,530
The right thing to do is
to fight Park Tae Ho,

95
00:04:54,630 --> 00:04:56,800
reveal the truth,
and make sure he's punished.

96
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,770
That might be right for you,

97
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,670
but it's not for me.

98
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:06,010
What if my whole life is ruined
because I stood up to the chairman?

99
00:05:06,710 --> 00:05:08,310
What if I step up
to reveal the truth...

100
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:10,720
and end up dead like my dad?

101
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:14,290
Not everyone wants to fight
like you do.

102
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:18,620
Some people care more
about the immediate payoff.

103
00:05:20,790 --> 00:05:24,400
Are you telling me that was a payoff
rather than a threat...

104
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:26,830
to trade your father's life...

105
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,530
and honor?

106
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:30,840
That's right.

107
00:05:31,670 --> 00:05:33,340
Nothing's going to bring
my dad back,

108
00:05:34,170 --> 00:05:35,770
and I have to find a way to survive.

109
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:39,410
Isn't that the realistic
and rational decision?

110
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:42,980
There are far more people
in this world...

111
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:45,020
who think and choose like I do.

112
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:46,450
Don't be ridiculous.

113
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:48,650
You're just making excuses...

114
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,390
because you're afraid
to stand up to Park Tae Ho.

115
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:54,030
So what if I'm afraid?

116
00:05:54,990 --> 00:05:57,300
Instead of fighting recklessly
like you,

117
00:05:58,130 --> 00:05:59,230
I'm going to survive.

118
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:01,870
By siding with the chairman,

119
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:04,300
I'll come out on top in the end.

120
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:26,090
Why did you come here in person?

121
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:32,500
I heard the news
of CEO Choi Sam Sik's passing.

122
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,300
With things as they are,

123
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:38,200
I felt I could no longer
remain silent.

124
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,770
Since the dead can't speak,

125
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:43,440
the living must reveal the truth.

126
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,840
The truth?

127
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:49,150
The Temi Bio incident
from seven years ago.

128
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:55,320
I'll tell you everything
I know about it.

129
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:59,890
About how Choi Sam Sik
murdered Baek Jun Gi...

130
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,960
down to the last detail.

131
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:20,610
What do you think you're doing?

132
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:25,050
If I want the truth to come out,

133
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:27,520
I need to go in
and face investigation myself.

134
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:28,650
And so?

135
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:32,020
Did you confess to killing
CEO Choi Sam Sik?

136
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:35,030
Did you tell them that
you killed CEO Baek Jun Gi...

137
00:07:35,090 --> 00:07:36,360
to cover up killing my mother,

138
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:39,560
piling one murder on top of another?
Did you tell them that truth?

139
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:42,570
That's not the truth.

140
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:47,470
It's just slander
from you and Baek Jin Ju...

141
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:49,640
who want to drag me down.

142
00:07:50,810 --> 00:07:52,040
That's the only truth here.

143
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:55,750
- Park Tae Ho.
- How dare you call your father...

144
00:07:57,380 --> 00:07:58,650
by name like that?

145
00:07:59,150 --> 00:08:02,490
How can I call
a monster like you "Father?"

146
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:06,920
How can I,
after you've killed again?

147
00:08:07,660 --> 00:08:11,460
Now, we're really through.

148
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,230
Wait.

149
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,270
Even so,

150
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,240
blood is thicker than water.

151
00:08:25,010 --> 00:08:26,910
I'm giving you one last chance,

152
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:29,210
so stop this and come back.

153
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,280
A chance?

154
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:36,590
The reinvestigation will be
wrapped up by the end of today,

155
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:39,590
and Kim Dan Hui and Baek Jin Ju
can't beat me.

156
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:42,990
Don't ruin your life
over a fight you can't win.

157
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:46,930
Come back as my son
and inherit Adele Group.

158
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,900
Compared to Hyun Jun,

159
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:54,410
you're the better choice after all.

160
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:06,050
You murdered my mother
and the father of the woman I love,

161
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:10,220
then kept killing
to hide what you did.

162
00:09:11,090 --> 00:09:13,220
I can't live with someone like you
as my father.

163
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:15,030
The Adele Group?

164
00:09:15,830 --> 00:09:16,860
Just...

165
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,960
give it all to Hyun Jun.

166
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:22,970
I don't need it.

167
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:36,380
It's me.

168
00:09:37,420 --> 00:09:40,750
The questioning will be over
by this evening.

169
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:43,650
Meanwhile,
handle everything concerning...

170
00:09:44,890 --> 00:09:46,420
the Temi Bio reinvestigation.

171
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:50,190
Clean up this mess completely
by the time I'm done here.

172
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:51,730
Right.

173
00:10:01,610 --> 00:10:02,710
So he'd rather have Min Jun...

174
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,240
than me?

175
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:17,620
Deputy Chief Yun, take this...

176
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:20,420
and put a complete stop
to the reinvestigation.

177
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:27,060
Once again, I'm amazed
by the chairman's generosity.

178
00:10:27,230 --> 00:10:29,500
Just go and make sure
everyone keeps their mouths shut.

179
00:10:29,770 --> 00:10:30,770
Get moving.

180
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:39,040
Geun Tae, as for you,

181
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:42,180
leak this to the press
and get the reporters talking.

182
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,750
Tell them Choi Sam Sik
is the actual culprit...

183
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:44,920
behind the incident seven years ago,

184
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:47,420
and Baek Jin Ju framed Park Tae Ho.

185
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:49,750
Spread that message loud and clear.

186
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:54,090
Are you not going to do it?
Should I do it myself?

187
00:11:03,970 --> 00:11:05,040
And this...

188
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,440
This one's for Ms. Choi.

189
00:11:27,430 --> 00:11:28,460
Yes, Director Seo.

190
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:32,060
My father's issue
will be resolved soon.

191
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:33,700
Once it is,

192
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:37,300
please bring up the election
of the new chairman.

193
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:39,340
Right, about Moon Tae Jin.

194
00:11:39,670 --> 00:11:41,870
Make sure the major shareholder
doesn't sway the other directors,

195
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:44,080
and keep everyone in line.

196
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,950
The chairmanship at Adele Group...

197
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:54,120
won't be going to your son,
Park Min Jun.

198
00:11:55,390 --> 00:11:57,050
It's going to be mine.

199
00:11:58,990 --> 00:12:00,690
I won't let anyone take it from me.

200
00:12:08,630 --> 00:12:10,400
You must be heartbroken.

201
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,000
I...

202
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:16,310
woke up this morning...

203
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:19,340
and made some rice.

204
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:21,310
I'm sure...

205
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:25,320
I heard him ask for his meal.

206
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:28,950
But he was gone.

207
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,560
I don't know where he went.

208
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:34,390
He's nowhere to be seen.

209
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:38,630
Oh, honey.

210
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:42,700
Oh dear.

211
00:12:45,370 --> 00:12:49,610
I know this is difficult,
but you must pull yourself together.

212
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:53,680
It's the only way
to clear CEO Choi's name.

213
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:56,950
Clear his name?

214
00:12:58,050 --> 00:12:59,080
First...

215
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:02,090
could you please
take a look at this?

216
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:06,320
The true culprit behind...

217
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:08,560
the Temi Bio case
from seven years ago is...

218
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,460
not Chairman Park Tae Ho,
but Choi Sam Sik,

219
00:13:10,830 --> 00:13:12,160
my father.

220
00:13:14,470 --> 00:13:17,330
What in the world
is that girl saying?

221
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:21,640
It looks like Ms. Choi
was used by Park Tae Ho again.

222
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:24,940
So, you're saying that Yu Na...

223
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:28,950
has made her own dead father
out to be a murderer?

224
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:31,980
Oh, my goodness. That crazy girl.

225
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:34,950
The skies will be furious.

226
00:13:35,020 --> 00:13:36,720
How could she do this
to her own father?

227
00:13:41,530 --> 00:13:42,790
How could she...

228
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:44,660
Before CEO Choi...

229
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,600
went to the police station,

230
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,970
Jin Ju and I met him in person.

231
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:52,040
He decided that,

232
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:55,240
even if it was late,
he'd reveal Park Tae Ho's crimes.

233
00:13:55,610 --> 00:13:58,740
We can't let his final wish
be destroyed like this.

234
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:03,680
We have to change Ms. Choi's mind.

235
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,520
If that's not possible,

236
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:08,720
please step forward
and testify yourself.

237
00:14:09,150 --> 00:14:12,690
Say that CEO Choi isn't a murderer
and that Park Tae Ho is.

238
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:15,190
Me?

239
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,230
Oh, dear.

240
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:19,430
Right now, I don't even know...

241
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:22,470
how I'm going to hold
my husband's funeral.

242
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,570
What can I possibly do alone?

243
00:14:26,500 --> 00:14:28,070
I don't have the strength for it.

244
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:33,480
Oh, dear. My poor husband.

245
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:35,950
You poor thing.

246
00:14:37,450 --> 00:14:40,180
Oh, dear.

247
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:51,800
Are we really just going
to leave her like this?

248
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,730
I want to take her
to the police station right now...

249
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:56,370
and have her testify.

250
00:14:56,670 --> 00:14:58,900
She hasn't even held
the funeral yet.

251
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:01,970
We can't drag a mother and daughter
to the police station...

252
00:15:01,970 --> 00:15:03,510
and make them fight.

253
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:05,310
Is that what would happen?

254
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,480
Is that why you didn't tell her...

255
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:10,280
he was likely murdered
by Park Tae Ho?

256
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:13,220
The autopsy results
will definitely be fabricated,

257
00:15:13,620 --> 00:15:16,420
and Ms. Choi is personally
covering up the incident.

258
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:17,860
I can't just throw out...

259
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:20,520
murder accusations
without any proof.

260
00:15:21,890 --> 00:15:23,830
It's best to wait
until after the funeral...

261
00:15:23,930 --> 00:15:25,800
and try to persuade her then.

262
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:29,900
What's this?

263
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:34,970
The gate was open,
so I wondered who was here.

264
00:15:35,270 --> 00:15:36,270
Was it you?

265
00:15:36,540 --> 00:15:39,010
Why? Are you talking
to Ms. Choi's mom...

266
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:41,780
to get her to change
her daughter's mind?

267
00:15:44,380 --> 00:15:47,890
A man is dead,
and you're acting like it's nothing,

268
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:51,060
just running errands
for Park Tae Ho?

269
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:54,890
You keep avoiding the question
about finding the slush fund ledger,

270
00:15:56,090 --> 00:15:58,060
and now you're helping him
cover his tracks?

271
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:03,330
If Park Tae Ho ends up in prison,

272
00:16:03,330 --> 00:16:05,570
Hyun Jun loses his chance
at the chairmanship.

273
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:07,000
My hands are tied.

274
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,710
To be honest, I'm tired of running
around with bags of money too.

275
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:13,840
I thought it would end
with Choi Sam Sik taking the fall.

276
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:17,350
I didn't know Park Tae Ho would
kill him just to shut him up.

277
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:22,790
What did you just say?

278
00:16:23,220 --> 00:16:25,760
Park Tae Ho killed him?

279
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:29,130
Are you saying Park Tae Ho
killed Yu Na's dad?

280
00:16:29,660 --> 00:16:30,660
What?

281
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,800
It seems like you didn't know that.

282
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:35,400
My gosh.

283
00:16:35,770 --> 00:16:37,770
What is this I'm hearing?

284
00:16:38,070 --> 00:16:40,100
What? Is there a problem?

285
00:16:40,770 --> 00:16:43,670
Ms. Choi knows everything
and is working with Park Tae Ho.

286
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,540
She was going to find out anyway.

287
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:50,210
Anyway, consider
the payment delivered.

288
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:55,720
- Oh, dear.
- Are you all right?

289
00:16:58,220 --> 00:17:00,960
Is everything that woman said true?

290
00:17:01,660 --> 00:17:03,960
Was Yu Na's dad killed
by Park Tae Ho,

291
00:17:04,930 --> 00:17:06,230
but Yu Na...

292
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:11,470
still teamed up with the murderer...

293
00:17:12,170 --> 00:17:14,840
to brand her own father a murderer?

294
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:17,140
My gosh.

295
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:18,910
Yes.

296
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:21,110
It's all true.

297
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,580
We don't have evidence yet,

298
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:27,480
but it seems CEO Choi...

299
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:31,320
was murdered by Park Tae Ho.

300
00:17:33,390 --> 00:17:34,390
As for Ms. Choi,

301
00:17:35,490 --> 00:17:38,800
she sided with Park Tae Ho
and gave false testimony.

302
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:43,470
Park Tae Ho did all of this
to cover up his own crimes.

303
00:17:43,870 --> 00:17:45,700
No. Oh, dear.

304
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:49,540
How... How could she?

305
00:17:49,670 --> 00:17:53,110
My gosh. My poor husband.

306
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:55,480
He'll be turning over in his grave.

307
00:17:56,010 --> 00:17:57,450
I can't believe it.

308
00:17:58,720 --> 00:18:00,880
My poor husband.

309
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:03,790
Chairman Park Tae Ho,
are you claiming innocence?

310
00:18:04,090 --> 00:18:06,860
- Please give us a statement.
- Hello, everyone.

311
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,690
- As multiple witnesses point...
- The true culprit...

312
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,330
to the late Choi Sam Sik
as the culprit in the Temi Bio case,

313
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:11,430
- is Choi Sam Sik.
- murder charges against...

314
00:18:11,430 --> 00:18:13,000
former Adele Group
Chairman Park Tae Ho...

315
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,000
have officially been dropped.

316
00:18:15,170 --> 00:18:16,400
Accordingly, the police announced...

317
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:19,270
that they will completely reconsider
a reinvestigation...

318
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,140
It's the same method
he used seven years ago.

319
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:25,280
He pays people off,
fabricates the case,

320
00:18:25,340 --> 00:18:27,710
and even controls the police
and the media.

321
00:18:27,850 --> 00:18:30,610
We have to stop them
from halting the reinvestigation.

322
00:18:31,150 --> 00:18:35,120
Of course. We'll mobilize
our entire legal team to fight this.

323
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:37,890
Yes, please buy us some time.

324
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,790
In the meantime, I'll find a way
to turn things around.

325
00:18:42,030 --> 00:18:44,630
Right. I'll do my best,

326
00:18:45,230 --> 00:18:47,500
but honestly, I'm worried
we won't find a way out of this.

327
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:48,970
Seriously.

328
00:18:49,330 --> 00:18:50,630
First Park Tae Ho, now Choi Yu Na.

329
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:52,370
I really can't believe
they went this far.

330
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,570
I can almost understand Park Tae Ho,
but how could Choi Yu Na do this?

331
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:58,080
How can she do this
knowing how her father died?

332
00:19:02,050 --> 00:19:04,620
If my dad had turned himself in
and gone to prison,

333
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:05,680
he wouldn't have died.

334
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:09,520
He died
because you pushed him to fight.

335
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:13,790
How are the funeral arrangements
coming along?

336
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:15,890
Since the autopsy results are out,

337
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:17,530
they'll be moving forward
with the funeral.

338
00:19:20,130 --> 00:19:22,900
I should go
and help out with the funeral.

339
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,470
In person?

340
00:19:25,340 --> 00:19:27,970
I doubt Choi Yu Na
will let you hang around.

341
00:19:28,570 --> 00:19:30,710
Still, I think I should go.

342
00:19:32,340 --> 00:19:36,450
Like Choi Yu Na said,
I feel bad for pushing him to fight.

343
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:41,450
I'll also check for more evidence
that could expose Choi Yu Na's lies.

344
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,740
Did you hear from the police?

345
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,340
The autopsy is over now,

346
00:20:07,140 --> 00:20:08,750
so we have to prepare
for the funeral.

347
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:13,850
How dare you speak of his funeral?

348
00:20:15,050 --> 00:20:16,720
After killing your own father,

349
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:20,220
how can you shamelessly pretend
to be a devoted daughter?

350
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:24,660
What are you talking about?
Didn't you hear the autopsy results?

351
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,930
Dad died from a heart attack...

352
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:35,640
Adele Group threw this at us
as payment for your father's life.

353
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:39,380
You disgust me.

354
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:41,480
How could you frame...

355
00:20:42,110 --> 00:20:45,080
your own father for murder
just for a quick payout?

356
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:49,490
How can you play nice
with Park Tae Ho...

357
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:51,120
after he murdered your own father?

358
00:20:52,820 --> 00:20:55,860
This isn't all I got.

359
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:58,230
I made sure I got more.

360
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,930
What did you just say?

361
00:21:00,930 --> 00:21:02,930
I've already received my stock,

362
00:21:03,230 --> 00:21:05,240
and I'm marrying Park Hyun Jun soon.

363
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:07,700
As the wife
of Adele Group's next chairman,

364
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:11,810
I'll be ruling
as the lady of the house.

365
00:21:11,810 --> 00:21:13,780
My gosh, you're insane.

366
00:21:14,310 --> 00:21:16,350
My own daughter
is out of her absolute mind!

367
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:25,890
Take all of this...

368
00:21:27,060 --> 00:21:29,460
and throw it back in their faces.

369
00:21:29,660 --> 00:21:31,360
I'm going to the police...

370
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:35,330
to tell them
that Park Tae Ho killed them all.

371
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:38,040
That he's the one
who killed CEO Baek, too!

372
00:21:38,170 --> 00:21:40,900
I'm going to tell them everything.
Get out of my way.

373
00:21:41,470 --> 00:21:43,110
Are you trying to get me killed too?

374
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:46,880
Choi Yu Na!

375
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,910
What do you think happens to me
if you go to the police?

376
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:51,850
To the rest of the world,

377
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:54,420
I'll be the daughter
who sold out her own father.

378
00:21:54,950 --> 00:21:58,660
And to Park Tae Ho,
I'll be someone he has to eliminate.

379
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:01,930
Just like how he killed Dad
to shut me up,

380
00:22:02,590 --> 00:22:04,090
he'll get rid of me.

381
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:07,030
Do you want me to be killed too?

382
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:11,700
Mom!

383
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:14,400
Get a grip.

384
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:16,970
Dad's already dead,

385
00:22:17,770 --> 00:22:21,110
and I'm the only one left
to take care of you.

386
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:25,680
With no way to support yourself,
you have to rely on me to survive.

387
00:22:32,620 --> 00:22:35,460
Like you said,
this is the price for Dad's life.

388
00:22:36,230 --> 00:22:37,790
Don't just throw it away.

389
00:22:39,030 --> 00:22:40,630
Just use it to deal
with the asset seizure.

390
00:22:43,630 --> 00:22:45,370
You can put that toward
the funeral costs as well.

391
00:22:48,340 --> 00:22:50,910
You're no longer my daughter.

392
00:22:54,180 --> 00:22:57,350
You don't need to come
to your father's funeral,

393
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:58,980
so get out of here.

394
00:23:00,050 --> 00:23:01,450
Get out of this house.

395
00:23:01,820 --> 00:23:03,490
Get out right now!

396
00:23:03,890 --> 00:23:04,920
Fine!

397
00:23:06,490 --> 00:23:09,230
Honestly, a funeral
would've been uncomfortable,

398
00:23:09,290 --> 00:23:10,630
so this is for the best.

399
00:23:11,090 --> 00:23:13,360
I wasn't planning on
staying here long anyway.

400
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:14,460
From here on out,

401
00:23:15,330 --> 00:23:17,330
I'm going to live
with the Adele family anyway.

402
00:23:20,170 --> 00:23:22,010
Oh my.

403
00:23:22,910 --> 00:23:23,940
My gosh.

404
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:26,140
Goodness me.

405
00:23:27,010 --> 00:23:28,780
Sam Sik, oh no.

406
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:32,680
Sam Sik, what do I do?

407
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:37,190
Honey, she's terrifying.

408
00:23:38,460 --> 00:23:42,360
What am I going to do
with my clueless daughter?

409
00:23:42,690 --> 00:23:44,560
Oh, dear.

410
00:23:52,470 --> 00:23:53,470
Right.

411
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:56,740
How is the reinvestigation
coming along?

412
00:23:57,370 --> 00:24:01,240
If there are no particular issues,
it should be concluded soon.

413
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:04,950
All right. Good work, everyone.

414
00:24:06,850 --> 00:24:09,050
The expenses for this
were rather high.

415
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,220
How much did we spend in total?

416
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:16,630
Including all the lobbying funds
and shares handed over to Ms. Choi,

417
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:20,360
- over 20 million dollars.
- Wait a minute.

418
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:23,870
You even gave shares to Ms. Choi?

419
00:24:28,070 --> 00:24:29,140
Hello.

420
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:41,750
So you're going after
Park Tae Ho's money?

421
00:24:45,460 --> 00:24:47,790
This experience made me
realize something.

422
00:24:48,090 --> 00:24:50,330
He may have lost
the chairmanship at the Adele Group,

423
00:24:50,660 --> 00:24:52,430
but that wasn't enough.

424
00:24:52,930 --> 00:24:55,530
Park Tae Ho uses money
to control people,

425
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,240
and I'm going to strip him
of that power too.

426
00:24:58,340 --> 00:25:01,870
You mean you're after
Park Tae Ho's slush fund.

427
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:03,440
Is that even possible?

428
00:25:04,070 --> 00:25:06,340
It all comes down
to turning one key person.

429
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:08,250
Which of Park Tae Ho's people...

430
00:25:08,980 --> 00:25:11,150
are you planning to turn?

431
00:25:14,120 --> 00:25:15,190
Ms. Choi,

432
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:18,150
you pocketed the money
and managed to snag shares too?

433
00:25:18,990 --> 00:25:19,990
Yes.

434
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:22,330
It's a little less than I expected,

435
00:25:22,860 --> 00:25:25,230
but it's enough to affect
the succession battle.

436
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:28,400
To become the chairman
of Adele Group,

437
00:25:28,830 --> 00:25:30,970
you're going to need my shares.

438
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:36,370
How could you make a decision
like this on your own?

439
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:37,910
Hold on.

440
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:40,240
Since when do I need permission
to do what I want...

441
00:25:40,710 --> 00:25:42,450
with my own shares?

442
00:25:42,510 --> 00:25:45,050
Because, as she said,
it affects the succession battle.

443
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:49,820
You don't need to worry.
After all, my shares...

444
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:51,720
are yours, Hyun Jun.

445
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:56,730
- What?
- You're part of my compensation.

446
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:03,230
Sir, when do you think
we should get married?

447
00:26:03,630 --> 00:26:06,640
I don't mind skipping the ceremony
and just registering our marriage.

448
00:26:11,410 --> 00:26:12,440
Unbelievable.

449
00:26:13,610 --> 00:26:15,080
You approved her marriage to me...

450
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:17,410
without even discussing it
with me first?

451
00:26:17,810 --> 00:26:21,280
You want to become chairman
of Adele Group, don't you?

452
00:26:21,790 --> 00:26:24,990
Look at this
as me giving you my shares.

453
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:29,560
Exactly.
Even your mother approved of it.

454
00:26:31,860 --> 00:26:32,860
Mom.

455
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:36,630
It's just a formality.

456
00:26:37,870 --> 00:26:38,970
Besides, this isn't even
your first marriage.

457
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:43,870
Then you won't mind
if I move in starting today, right?

458
00:26:52,820 --> 00:26:54,120
Manager Kang?

459
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,920
You mean Park Tae Ho's
personal assistant?

460
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:58,920
Yes.

461
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:03,530
We need Manager Kang
to access the slush fund account.

462
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:05,930
Although the time was short,

463
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:08,800
I learned something while managing
Park Tae Ho's slush fund.

464
00:27:09,230 --> 00:27:10,800
His slush fund is sitting...

465
00:27:11,230 --> 00:27:14,270
in a dummy account
under Manager Kang's name.

466
00:27:14,540 --> 00:27:17,510
Only Park Tae Ho knows the password.

467
00:27:17,570 --> 00:27:19,280
Being a suspicious man,

468
00:27:19,910 --> 00:27:22,980
he wouldn't have shared
the password with anyone.

469
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:27,480
However, if Manager Kang decides
he wants that account,

470
00:27:27,750 --> 00:27:31,420
he can do whatever he wants
since it's in his name.

471
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:34,020
He could just reset the password...

472
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:36,430
and pocket the entire slush fund.

473
00:27:36,630 --> 00:27:37,630
But...

474
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:42,030
he's been by Park Tae Ho's side
for a long time.

475
00:27:43,170 --> 00:27:44,430
Would he really change his mind?

476
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:46,540
I'm going to remind him...

477
00:27:47,340 --> 00:27:49,340
exactly what kind of person
Park Tae Ho is.

478
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:53,080
His years of devotion
will turn into regret,

479
00:27:53,910 --> 00:27:57,310
and he'll realize that Park Tae Ho
could have him killed.

480
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:07,220
I guess it's too soon
to share a bedroom, right?

481
00:28:10,330 --> 00:28:12,930
I'll stay in Min Jun's old room
until the wedding.

482
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:15,230
Forget the wedding...

483
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:18,200
and focus on the funeral first.

484
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,640
If you're done
exploiting your father's death,

485
00:28:22,310 --> 00:28:23,940
the least you can do
is go beg for forgiveness.

486
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:26,080
Teaming up
with your father's killer,

487
00:28:26,510 --> 00:28:28,380
smiling over your new shares...

488
00:28:29,180 --> 00:28:30,280
and a promised wedding?

489
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:34,420
You make me want to throw up.

490
00:28:35,390 --> 00:28:37,150
Where do you get off
acting so righteous?

491
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:41,860
You despise
your own chauffeur father...

492
00:28:42,290 --> 00:28:43,560
while playing the chairman's son,

493
00:28:43,790 --> 00:28:45,960
eyeing Adele Group like it's yours.

494
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,200
You and I are the same.

495
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:51,230
At the end of the day, our own lives
come before our parents.

496
00:28:52,070 --> 00:28:54,670
Doesn't that make us
a perfect match for marriage?

497
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:57,840
Stop pretending to be
so nice and righteous.

498
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:00,140
If you want to keep your secret,

499
00:29:00,740 --> 00:29:02,580
just shut it
and prepare for the wedding.

500
00:29:29,110 --> 00:29:30,410
Thank you, Jin Ju.

501
00:29:31,910 --> 00:29:33,740
With you standing by me
like my own daughter,

502
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:35,650
we managed to get through
the funeral.

503
00:29:36,180 --> 00:29:38,250
Thank you so much. I mean it.

504
00:29:39,350 --> 00:29:40,420
Not at all.

505
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:42,650
You must be exhausted
from the funeral.

506
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,050
Please get some rest.

507
00:29:44,420 --> 00:29:45,420
Sure.

508
00:29:49,290 --> 00:29:50,790
(Korean National Police Agency)

509
00:29:55,170 --> 00:29:57,470
These must be Mr. Choi's belongings.

510
00:29:57,830 --> 00:30:00,440
Yes, I need to go through them,

511
00:30:02,070 --> 00:30:04,970
but I can't bring myself
to open the box alone.

512
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:08,480
Since I'm here,
I'll organize them before I go.

513
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:11,680
I couldn't ask that of you.
You must be tired, too.

514
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:13,580
I'm fine.

515
00:30:27,660 --> 00:30:30,470
We were on the phone
right before he died.

516
00:30:31,870 --> 00:30:33,900
He told me he was heading
into the interrogation room,

517
00:30:34,900 --> 00:30:39,210
ready to confess
that Park Tae Ho gave the orders.

518
00:30:39,980 --> 00:30:42,380
Not knowing
he'd be murdered in cold blood...

519
00:30:43,710 --> 00:30:44,710
Did he say...

520
00:30:45,350 --> 00:30:46,750
Park Tae Ho gave all the orders,

521
00:30:47,250 --> 00:30:50,150
and that he'd spill everything
to the police?

522
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:52,620
Yes, he did.

523
00:30:53,990 --> 00:30:58,130
Could that last call
have been recorded? May I check?

524
00:30:58,230 --> 00:30:59,230
Go ahead.

525
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:09,470
I'm not taking the fall
for Chairman Park.

526
00:31:09,770 --> 00:31:12,640
I'm going to tell the truth
that he ordered everything.

527
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:16,780
What?

528
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:22,120
Wait. What is this?

529
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:24,120
How can a dead man...

530
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:29,630
Hello? Who are you?
Tell me who you are!

531
00:31:30,990 --> 00:31:32,830
It's a file
from Choi Sam Sik's phone.

532
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:36,300
If you want to get rid of it,
do as I say.

533
00:31:36,930 --> 00:31:39,240
Wait. What?

534
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:45,640
What the...

535
00:32:14,770 --> 00:32:17,810
(Pearl in Red)

536
00:32:17,870 --> 00:32:19,510
What happens if this gets out?

537
00:32:19,940 --> 00:32:22,780
I thought it was all over.
Will he be arrested again?

538
00:32:23,010 --> 00:32:27,150
Yu Na, it's still not too late.
Even now...

539
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:28,280
Choi Yu Na.

540
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:29,750
The funeral's over, so that's that.

541
00:32:29,750 --> 00:32:31,690
You've got to let it go
and move on, Mom.

542
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:33,220
- Yes, sir.
- Kick Min Jun out...

543
00:32:33,220 --> 00:32:36,790
and make it clear to everyone
that I'm your son and heir.

544
00:32:36,860 --> 00:32:40,200
That's all you want from me
in return?

545
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,130
I want to be, solely and completely,

546
00:32:42,670 --> 00:32:44,030
your son.

547
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,600
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
